<title type="html"><![CDATA[10/6(Thu) Arguments for and against capital punishment/ 10 Tips for Enjoying Your Class Reunion (Host: Louie)]]></title>

<content type="html" xml:base="http://www.royalclub.tw/bbs3/viewtopic.php?t=658&amp;p=686#p686"><![CDATA[
10/6(Thu) Arguments for and against capital punishment/ 10 Tips for Enjoying Your Class Reunion (Host: Louie)<br /><br />Agenda:<br />7:00-7:10 pm Opening Remarks<br />7:05-7:40 pm Session 1: Group Discussion<br />7:40-8:00 pm Individual Presentation<br />8:00-8:05 pm Break<br />8:05-8:40 pm Session 2: Group Discussion<br />8:40-9:00 pm Individual Presentation<br /><br />We will hold a zoom meeting only.<br /><br />Zoom meeting: Please click the link below<br /><br /><!-- m --><a class="postlink" href="https://zoomtw.zoom.us/j/92987266213?pw">https://zoomtw.zoom.us/j/92987266213?pw</a><!-- m --> ...<br />Meeting ID:929 8726 6213<br />Password:112233<br /><br />-------------------------------------------- <br /><br />Session 1: Arguments for and against capital punishment<br /><br /><!-- m --><a class="postlink" href="https://www.britannica.com/topic/capital-punishment/Arguments-for-and-against-capital-punishment">https://www.britannica.com/topic/capita ... punishment</a><!-- m --><br /><!-- m --><a class="postlink" href="https://onyourpsy.com/20200416-1/">https://onyourpsy.com/20200416-1/</a><!-- m --><br /><br />Questions<br />1.Are you pro or anti capital punishment (death penalty)? What are the reasons?<br />2.There is an abolitionist group in R.O.C called Taiwan Alliance to End the Death Penalty (TAEDP). Every time when serious criminal cases happened,  the public clamor for death penalty and then TAEDP will assert their attitude against it. Do you know their claims?<br />3.There is a point of view in the article about utilitarian: “the death penalty is not a more effective deterrent than the alternative sanction of life or long-term imprisonment”. Or  simply “killing can’t prevent killing （以殺不能止殺）”. Do you agree?<br />4.Usually the justice on court rules out death penalty to the defendant based on reason called “possibility of edification （教化）”. Here I attach a weblink in Chinese discussing about edification. Please share your thoughts about the possibility of edification.<br /><br /><br /><br />Session 2: 10 Tips for Enjoying Your Class Reunion<br /><br /><!-- m --><a class="postlink" href="https://guideposts.org/positive-living/friends-and-family/friends/10-tips-for-enjoying-your-class-reunion/">https://guideposts.org/positive-living/ ... s-reunion/</a><!-- m --><br /><br />Questions:<br />1.Did you join a class reunion recently? When and what was it? Did you enjoy? If you never join a class reunion, why?<br />2.What could daunt you or embarrass you in a class reunion? Can you have a new eye and forgiving heart toward your old classmates?<br />3.Do you compare yourself to your classmates about your circumstances? What about if you feel inferior/superior?<br />4.In 30 years or more the look of a person could vary a lot. Anything interesting? What do you usually do to recall each other about the past?<br /><br /><br />P.S.<br />1.參加三次(含實體及線上會議)後，只要繳交1,000元(學生500元)，即可成為ROYAL終身會員!<br />2.請帶著開放的心與熱情來參加全英文會話聚會!<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://www.royalclub.tw/bbs3/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=38674">Louie Wang</a> — Sat Oct 01, 2022 11:21 am</p><hr />
]]></content>
